instructions_text: This experiment is about your beliefs about relatedness as depicted by scatterplots.
instructions: NA

instructions: NA

instructions_text: Then, you will be shown a series of 45 scatterplots. Scatterplots depict the level of relatedness between variables.
instructions: NA

instructions_text: This relatedness is often measured on a scale between 0 (not related at all) and 1 (extremely related).
instructions: NA

instructions_text: The graphs you will see have been taken from a well-known British news source. The identity of this source has been obscured at their request.
instructions: NA

instructions_text: Once you have rated each scatterplot, press the spacebar to move onto the next trial.
instructions: NA

instructions_text: You will now have the chance to practice rating graphs using the sliding scale.
